# Unit plane (xz, +Y up) as a single quad with explicit UV corners.
# Winding order is CCW viewed from +Y so the angle-weighted smooth normal
# at every vertex of the subdivided plane points outward (+Y) and the
# scalar displacement pushes the surface above y=0 by default.
#
# Source for the scalar-displacement showcase (step 3/5 of the surface
# displacement stack). The quad is intentionally a single 4-corner face so
# Catmull-Clark / Loop subdivision can refine it uniformly without the
# triangulation seam a triangulated quad would introduce.
v -1.0  0.0 -1.0
v -1.0  0.0  1.0
v  1.0  0.0  1.0
v  1.0  0.0 -1.0
vt 0.0 0.0
vt 0.0 1.0
vt 1.0 1.0
vt 1.0 0.0
f 1/1 2/2 3/3 4/4
